
    - Filters in AngularJS used to format the Application Data.

    - We Have Two Types Of Filters

        1. Predefined Filters

        2. Custom Filters

Predefined Filters.

        - The Filters Given by the Framework Called as Predefined Filter.


1. uppercase

    - used to convert the lowercase characters to uppercase.

Ex.

    {{'hello' | uppercase}} //HELLO


2. lowercase

    - used to convert uppercase characters to lowercase.

Ex.

    {{"HEELO" | lowercase }}  //hello


3. currency

    - it is used to append the "$" symbol to the numerical value.


    {{100 | currency}}    //$100.00


4. limitTo








    <table border="1">

        <tr>
            <th>id</th>
            <th>name</th>
            <th>rank</th>
        </tr>


        <tr ng-repeat="x in arry | orderBy:'-id' | limitTo:2">

            <td>{{x.id}}</td>
            <td>{{x.name}}</td>
            <td>{{x.rank}}</td>

        </tr>
    </table>



6. filter

    - This Filter used to search the table based on user input


 <tr ng-repeat="x in array | orderBy:'id' |
                             limitTo:2 |
                             filter:'AngularJS'">

            <td>{{x.id}}</td>
            <td>{{x.name}}</td>
            <td>{{x.rank}}</td>

        </tr>



7. date

        - used to format the Date Accroding to Application Requirement

        {{new Date() | date:'dd-MM-yy'}}

        {{new Date() | date:'MM-dd-yyyy'}}

        {{new Date() | date:'short'}}

        {{new Date() | date:'medium'}}

        {{new Date() | date:'fullDate'}}



CustomFilters
-

    - Creating Our own filter, based on Application Requirement Called as Custom Filter.


Ex.

    {{"welcome" | reverse }}

    app.filter("reverse" , reverse);
    function reverse(){
        return function(arg1}{
            var data="";
            for(var i=0;i<8;i++){
                data = arg1[i]+data;
            }
            return data;
        }
    }

